rows.label: qst200905_msg002
rows.name: Otto? What do you need him for?

rows.label: qst200905_msg003
rows.name:
It's about the windmill down at Tilly
Bakery. It's kind of broken...

rows.label: qst200905_msg004
rows.name:
We've been asked to get Otto
to come round and take a look.

rows.label: qst200905_msg006
rows.name:
How'd you like the bread? Ahato makes
some amazing sweets too. He's a bit of
a local celebrity.

rows.label: qst200905_msg007
rows.name: I go there a lot, myself.

rows.label: qst200905_msg010
rows.name:
Well, Otto's not back from his
logging shift yet.

rows.label: qst200905_msg011
rows.name:
Which is odd, 'cos he would normally
be finished by now...

rows.label: qst200905_msg012
rows.name: I hope nothing's happened to him...

rows.label: qst200905_msg013
rows.name:
We'll have a look for him. Could you
tell us where he went?

rows.label: qst200905_msg014
rows.name:
Yeah, sure. He went to the Nocclia
Timber Site.

rows.label: qst200905_msg019
rows.name:
Something might've happened to
him on the road.

rows.label: qst200905_msg020
rows.name:
Could you head up to the Nocclia
Timber Site and keep an eye out
for him on your way there?

rows.label: qst200905_msg021
rows.name:
I'm sure you lot'll be fine out there,
but worst comes to worst, you save
your own skins, OK?

rows.label: qst200905_msg022
rows.name: All right. Thanks for the help!

rows.label: qst200905_msg023
rows.name:
OK guys, let's go! The hunt for Otto
continues!
